#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Why is it best to clean your data?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:19
msgid "to make them as fit for use as possible"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:20
msgid "to achieve your data quality goals"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:23
msgid ""
"You should always aim to manage and publish data with the highest possible "
"quality.  This will improve your day-to-day work (it is easier to work with "
"organized and clean data), as well as the work of potential re-users of your "
"data, who need to understand them and trust their source before using them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "*How should you organize your data cleaning workflow?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:27
msgid "ask your colleagues for expertise"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:28
msgid "work at an institutional level to harmonize data quality workflows"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:30
msgid ""
"Nobody is expected to know everything about biodiversity data; you should "
"seek help and advice from your colleagues or other knowledgeable people, and "
"ensure that you're applying the good practices recommended by your "
"institution as you clean your data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Which is best:*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:34
msgid "prevent errors from occurring"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:35
msgid "correct errors as soon as you find them in your database or spreadsheet"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:37
msgid ""
"The best way to avoid spreading errors in your data is to prevent them from "
"occurring at the start of the data collecting/recording process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:39
msgid ""
"Of course, mistakes are unavoidable so you should also clean them as soon as "
"you find them, and document the cleaning process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:41
msgid ""
"If you don't have the time or resources to properly clean your data, it is "
"best to wait before you can do so instead of publishing erroneous data that "
"might confuse people."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Whose responsibility is data quality?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:45
msgid "Everyone involved in the management of data"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:47
msgid ""
"Every person involved in your data management workflow is at least partly "
"responsible for their quality, from the field technicians to the database "
"manager(s)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:49
msgid ""
"People who might later use your data can inform you of any remaining error "
"in your data, and should use them responsibly for their own research, but "
"the initial data quality is not their responsibility."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:51
msgid ""
"GBIF can perform automatic checks on your data (e.g. detection of missing "
"values, geographic outliers, unknown scientific names) but should not be "
"held responsible for errors that occurred earlier in the data management "
"process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Which tools can be used to clean your data?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:55
msgid "Excel & other spreadsheets management tools"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:57
msgid "Your database software"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:58
msgid "Online tools such as Scientific Names Resolver or Google Maps"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:60
msgid ""
"All kinds of tools can be used to clean your data, but you should identify "
"which ones will answer your needs in terms of taxonomic resolving, "
"georeferencing, deleting duplicates, and so on. You can find <<helpful-tools,"
"helpful tools>> listed in the data management section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "Data publishing review solutions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:64
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "*What does data publishing mean in the context of GBIF?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:66
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:87
msgid ""
"Making your biodiversity dataset(s) publicly accessible and discoverable in "
"a standardized format"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:68
msgid ""
"Data publishing within GBIF means making your biodiversity dataset(s) "
"publicly accessible in a standardized format (most of the time, Darwin "
"Core), so that it can be discovered and reused by other people."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "*What is an IPT?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:72
msgid "a tool that helps you publish your data to GBIF"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:73
msgid "a tool that helps you produce a Data paper"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:76
msgid ""
"The IPT (Integrated Publishing Toolkit) is a Java-coded software that allows "
"you to upload and publish data to GBIF.  It is not to be used as a data "
"management or data cleaning tool."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:78
msgid ""
"The IPT can also help you with the process of writing and submitting a data "
"paper, thanks to the EML file it generates automatically when you fill in "
"the metadata for your data resource."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Which Creative Commons licences and waivers are recommended by GBIF for data publication?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:82
msgid "CC0, CC-BY and CC-BY-NC"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:85
msgid ""
"The Creative Commons licences and waivers recommended to publish your "
"dataset(s) to GBIF are CC0, CC-BY and CC-BY-NC.  They are widely recognized "
"licenses and/or waivers that align with international open-data requirements "
"for data sharing and re-use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:87
msgid ""
"Please note that you should only choose CC0 or CC-BY waiver/license for your "
"BID-related dataset(s)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:89
#, no-wrap
msgid "*What are the three Cores from which you can choose for an IPT resource?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:91
msgid "Occurrence Core, Taxon Core, Event Core"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:93
msgid ""
"You can choose one of the three following Cores for each of your IPT "
"resources: Occurrence, Taxon or Event Core."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:95
msgid ""
"The Darwin Core standard also allows you to link extensions to your chosen "
"Core, such as SimpleMultimedia or MeasurementOrFact."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:97
msgid ""
"The metadata are filled in a separate section of the IPT and are shared "
"using the EML standard, not the Darwin Core (which is used for data only)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:99
#, no-wrap
msgid "*How many Extensions files can a dataset have?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:101
msgid "as many as needed"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:104
msgid ""
"Once you have chosen a Core for your IPT resource, you can add Darwin core "
"extensions to it.  You can add only one or several extensions, depending on "
"the type of Core you chose, and which extensions are compatible with it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:106
msgid ""
"Extensions are not mandatory (you can publish a dataset without any "
"extension) but can be useful if you want to share additional information "
"that you could not map with your chosen Core."
msgstr ""

